When a page loads, it requests font files (.woff, .woff2, .ttf, .otf) from servers, and these requests appear in the Network panel. This method intercepts these requests and allows direct access to the font files."}]

This method is particularly useful for older versions of Chrome where the Application tab might not have the Fonts section, or when you need to see fonts in the context of their source files.
